{"parentUuid":"657137b9-fb51-4387-8d01-1f7a44d110e8","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y4W1ryLhpV97aZyamFj3DG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":177,"cache_read_input_tokens":16391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":177},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZXRpR4ctxcCEUBqrXiqR","type":"assistant","uuid":"70765090-cf38-4be9-a244-fde571e1d079","timestamp":"2026-03-29T13:12:02.834Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/tymoyato","sessionId":"c1c5fd05-456f-486b-be09-75ef509e5d55","version":"2.1.85","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"lucky-discovering-thunder"}
{"parentUuid":"70765090-cf38-4be9-a244-fde571e1d079","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y4W1ryLhpV97aZyamFj3DG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Your setup: **RTX 2070** on a desktop with **Ryzen 7 3800X** — and the 3800X has **no integrated graphics**. This means:\n\n**You cannot disconnect/disable the NVIDIA card** — it's your only display output. Without it, you'd have no video signal at all.\n\nThe good news: it's only drawing **~10.5W at idle**, which is already quite low. The 215W limit is just the max under full load.\n\nIf you want to reduce that idle power further, you can enable NVIDIA's runtime power management:\n\n```bash\n# Enable runtime PM (allows the GPU to enter a lower power state when idle)\nsudo nano /etc/modprobe.d/nvidia.conf\n```\n\nAdd:\n```\noptions nvidia NVreg_DynamicPowerManagement=0x02\n```\n\nThen:\n```bash\nsudo mkinitcpio -P  # (Arch Linux)\nsudo reboot\n```\n\nAfter reboot, enable runtime suspension:\n```bash\nsudo bash -c 'echo \"auto\" > /sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:26:00.0/power/control'\n```\n\nThis can drop idle consumption to **~5W or less** when no display compositing is happening. But at 10.5W idle, it's already not a big concern unless you're trying to minimize power consumption significantly."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":177,"cache_read_input_tokens":16391,"output_tokens":584,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":177,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZXRpR4ctxcCEUBqrXiqR","type":"assistant","uuid":"84a5973f-209f-4d93-acda-b399a5b25f8f","timestamp":"2026-03-29T13:12:09.197Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/tymoyato","sessionId":"c1c5fd05-456f-486b-be09-75ef509e5d55","version":"2.1.85","gi