{"parentUuid":"20b56cbb-3238-4349-81b6-538e4c818eef","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CGt7n65iAruono1QvqPZFn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Correct — if the screen is showing anything (desktop, terminal, etc.), the GPU is actively compositing/rendering. That \"active\" status in the runtime PM confirms it's working.\n\nThe 10.5W you saw **is** the light-use draw (desktop rendering, no 3D load). True idle would only happen if:\n- The screen is **turned off** (monitor off, not just locked)\n- Or the GPU is offloaded to a secondary card while another renders the display (not possible in your setup)\n\nSo for your desktop with a single GPU driving the display, **~10W is essentially the floor** while the machine is running with a screen on. Not much to optimize there."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":596,"cache_read_input_tokens":16568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":596},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZXSuoJqrE2p66gtgcTS1","type":"assistant","uuid":"708c8cc9-bfb6-4c8a-96d5-b7187608b6bb","timestamp":"2026-03-29T13:26:27.065Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/tymoyato","sessionId":"c1c5fd05-456f-486b-be09-75ef509e5d55","version":"2.1.85","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"lucky-discovering-thunder"}
