{"parentUuid":"c7360381-d355-45ed-b221-c4e61f9e1e45","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016JTy6j94eXFRG3dLQwSdGm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In theory yes — a low-end GPU (like a GT 1030 or RX 6400) idles at **3-5W**. You could:\n\n- Plug display into the cheap card\n- Keep the RTX 2070 for gaming/compute, power it off when not needed\n\nBut problems with your setup:\n- **Ryzen 3800X has no iGPU** — you'd need to buy a second physical card\n- **Savings: ~5-7W** — very small, probably not worth the cost of a second card\n- Managing two GPUs on Linux adds complexity (switching between them for games)\n\n**Honest assessment:** not worth it. You'd spend €50-100 on a second GPU to save ~5W, which is less than €5/year in electricity. The RTX 2070 at 10W idle is already efficient for what it is.\n\nIf power consumption is a bigger concern, the larger wins are elsewhere — CPU, storage, fans."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":147,"cache_read_input_tokens":17549,"output_tokens":515,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":147,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZXSyi1DUnQXw6ugLNZpg","type":"assistant","uuid":"6e3a48e4-b6bc-41b9-921e-6468ac9e4333","timestamp":"2026-03-29T13:27:21.845Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/tymoyato","sessionId":"c1c5fd05-456f-486b-be09-75ef509e5d55","version":"2.1.85","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"lucky-discovering-thunder"}
